@node "Intro" "Introduction"
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
                              @{b}Introduction@{ub}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Imagine:  you're  writing an email and need one of those foreign chars
that  is  not  on  your U.K. keymap, you're typing on IRC and you want
one  of  the  fun  comedy  chars  you see people using, or you're just
writing a letter and you want the new Euro symbol. What do you do?

Well,  you hit the hotkey for Latin Map, of course! It is a simple MUI
window  that  gives  you access to those displayable characters not on
the  usual  U.K. keyboard and so usually impossible to type, much like
the Special Character window available in Microsoft Word.

As of v1.1 we have implemented a clip unit slider and a tab chain!
@endnode
@node "Req" "Requirements"
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
                              @{b}Requirements@{ub}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

 @{b}1)@{ub} OS 2.0+

 @{b}2)@{ub} MUI Release 3.8

And that really is all!

@endnode
@node "Use" "Using Latin Map"
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
                           @{b}Using Latin Map@{ub}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

 @{b}ToolTypes@{ub}

CLIPUNIT         ...number of clipboard unit to use (0-255). Default 0.

 @{b}CLI Parameters@{ub}

CLIPUNIT=0/N     ...number of clipboard unit to use (0-255). Default 0.


 @{b}Using Latin Map@{ub}

Ideally, run the program in your startup or WBStartup because then you
can  just  call  it to any screen at any time using the MUI hotkey and
«Frontmost»  screen  setting.  @{b}Note:  MUI  requires you to restart the
application for a hotkey setting to be recognised.@{ub}

The  window  is  a  simple  grid of 12x8 buttons, each with one of the
special characters in it. Click on a button and that character will be
copied  to  the  clipboard  unit  specified for you to paste into your
application.  @{b} Note:  some  chars  may appear as a "no such character"
box  if  your chosen font does not include them, but all characters in
Latin  Map  should  be displayable. This includes the top left button,
which should be the Euro symbol, because many old fonts do not support
it.@{ub}
@endnode
